From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Galileo CSM Workspace <galileo-csm@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 17:40:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] QuarkPlatformPkg: enter boot manager on boot

Force the platform boot manager to enter the firmware UI so legacy CSM
boot options are visible without an existing BootNext/BootOrder selection.

Keep legacy Boot#### variables compatible with GenericBds and rEFInd by
storing BBS_TABLE plus BbsIndex optional data. Existing two-byte
BbsIndex-only options are accepted and migrated instead of deleted.

Publish USB mass-storage devices that edk2 already connected as CSM BBS
hard-disk entries. This bridges UEFI USB BlockIo media to legacy boot
candidate discovery without running SeaBIOS USB discovery while the boot
manager refreshes options.

